<doc f='TrinityCore3.3.5/src/server/game/Spells/Auras/SpellAuraEffects.cpp' l='45'>//
// EFFECT HANDLER NOTES
//
// in aura handler there should be check for modes:
// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL set
// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK set
// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK set - aura is recalculated or is just applied/removed - need to redo all things related to m_amount
// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK - logical or of above conditions
// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_STAT - set when stats are reapplied
// such checks will speedup trinity change amount/send for client operations
// because for change amount operation packets will not be send
// aura effect handlers shouldn&apos;t contain any AuraEffect or Aura object modifications</doc>
<def f='TrinityCore6.x/src/server/game/Spells/Auras/SpellAuraEffects.cpp' l='60' type='pAuraEffectHandler [484]'/>
